        "high_temperature_liquid_flame": {
            "type": "task",
            "description": "高温液体火焰",
            "context_analysis": "The 'high_temperature_liquid_flame' feature refers to a fire caused by the combustion of high-temperature liquid substances. Such scenarios are highly hazardous due to the intense heat and fluidity of the burning material, which can spread rapidly and cause secondary hazards.",
            "subtask_gen_analysis": "Responding to a high-temperature liquid flame requires a sequence of actions: first, inspect the scene to assess the fire's extent and potential spread. Solid spray (such as powder or dry ice) can be used to suppress the flames and lower the temperature. Cleanup is essential to remove residual hazards, and throwing fire extinguishing bombs or laying asbestos felt can provide additional suppression and isolation. Monitoring and detection ensure the fire is fully controlled and no hidden dangers remain.",
            "dep_task_types": [],
            "basic_required_skills": [
