            "type": "task",
            "description": "高压电气火焰",
            "context_analysis": "The 'high-voltage_electrical_flame' feature refers to fires caused by high-voltage electrical equipment. These scenarios are dangerous due to the risk of electric shock, rapid fire spread, and the need for specialized extinguishing agents.",
            "subtask_gen_analysis": "To address a high-voltage electrical flame, first operate switches to cut off power and reduce risk. Use appropriate liquid sprays (such as foam or water) and build fire dikes to contain the fire. Gas sprays with inert gas can further suppress combustion. Inspection and monitoring are essential throughout to ensure safety and complete extinguishment.",
